definition:
γνώμη, -ης, ἡ 
 (γιγνώσκω), [in LXX: Da TH 2:15 (דָּת), Ps 82(83):3 (סוֹד), elsewhere, chiefly II Es, for טְעֵם ;] 
   1. a means of knowing, a token (Theogn.). 
   2. In Attic writers, the mind, its operations and results (see Edwards, Lex., App., A); 
  (a) mind, understanding; 
   (b) purpose, intention: Act.20:3; 
   (with) judgment, opinion: 1Co.1:10, Rev.17:13; 
   (d) counsel, advice: 1Co.7:25, 40 2Co.8:10, Phm 14; 
   (e) royal purpose, decree (as in Da, I and II Es): Rev.17:17 (Cremer, 671).
 † (AS)
